*What's the name of your project?
DCBA

*How should we categorize your project? (Note: The FSA review team may reassign categories if necessary.)
Products and Services

*What problem are you trying to solve through your project?
3D scanning has a wide variety of applications, from manufacturing verification to art preservation, but the high cost of accurate 3D scanners keeps this technology from being used in many of these potential applications.  We realized if we could bring down the cost and complexity of accurate 3D scanning, we could enable the use of 3D scanning in many applications where it now would be prohibitively expensive: research labs, hobbyist builders, 3D printing enthusiasts, artists, independent product designers, small manufacturers, etc.

We found that there was an academically popular technology, structured light scanning, that maintained high scan accuracy at lower costs. There is typically a large degree of complexity in setting up a structured light scanner, so if we could streamline this service and package it into a plug-and-play device, we could sell the product to many markets that currently cannot access 3D scanning. Additionally, we saw that we could make a product even less expensive than the typical structured light scanner by substituting inexpensive components in clever ways.

In summary, we want to bring 3D scanning to a large group of users who cannot access it today.  We will do this by building a low-cost, user-friendly, and high-accuracy 3D scanner.

*Tweet us your elevator pitch -- give us your elevator pitch in 140 characters or less.
DCBA's low-cost, high-quality 3D scanners enable fast & accurate modeling for research, design, art & manufacturing on a budget

